328
00:17:06,584 --> 00:17:07,699
Fine.

329
00:17:08,344 --> 00:17:11,142
You can show that last one
to the Minister.

330
00:17:11,304 --> 00:17:13,181
He'll be quiet fora bit.

331
00:17:15,424 --> 00:17:17,062
Is something the matter?

332
00:17:17,264 --> 00:17:18,856
Well, it's just that...

333
00:17:19,424 --> 00:17:21,574
I've been increasingly
worried about

334
00:17:21,744 --> 00:17:23,735
keeping things back
from the Minister.

335
00:17:23,904 --> 00:17:25,895
- Shall I...
- No, no, no.

336
00:17:26,064 --> 00:17:27,463
What do you mean?

337
00:17:27,624 --> 00:17:31,378
Why shouldn't he be allowed
to know things ifhe wants to?

338
00:17:31,544 --> 00:17:32,977
Silly Boy!

339
00:17:34,064 --> 00:17:38,740
Bernard, this country is governed
by Ministers making decisions

340
00:17:38,904 --> 00:17:41,099
from the various
alternative proposals

341
00:17:41,264 --> 00:17:43,653
- thatwe offerthem, is it not?
- Oh, yes.

342
00:17:43,904 --> 00:17:44,939
Well...

343
00:17:46,144 --> 00:17:48,374
If they had all the facts,

344
00:17:48,544 --> 00:17:51,456
they'd see all sorts
of otherpossibilities.

345
00:17:51,664 --> 00:17:53,814
They might even formulate
theirown plans

346
00:17:53,984 --> 00:17:56,817
instead of choosing between
the ones thatwe put up.

347
00:17:56,984 --> 00:17:58,940
- Would that matter?
- Would it matter!

348
00:17:59,104 --> 00:18:00,104
But why?

349
00:18:00,264 --> 00:18:03,813
As long as we can formulate
ourown proposals, we can

350
00:18:04,544 --> 00:18:06,853
guide them
to the correct decision.

351
00:18:07,024 --> 00:18:08,855
Can we? How?

352
00:18:10,584 --> 00:18:12,893
It's like a conjuror.

353
00:18:13,584 --> 00:18:15,097
The Three Card Trick.

354
00:18:15,264 --> 00:18:18,654
"Take any card", they pick
the one that you intend.

355
