371
00:19:12,264 --> 00:19:15,813
- What about yourman?
- I'm giving him plenty to read.

372
00:19:15,984 --> 00:19:17,576
Shouldn't you showhim

373
00:19:17,744 --> 00:19:20,463
the positive virtues
ofbeing kept ignorant?

374
00:19:20,624 --> 00:19:24,014
Lfhe doesn't know that
after 20 years as a politician...

375
00:19:44,184 --> 00:19:48,223
- You look worried, Bernard.
- I've just found this letter.

376
00:19:48,384 --> 00:19:50,261
I don't know
if I should open it.

377
00:19:50,424 --> 00:19:51,823
You know the rules.

378
00:19:51,984 --> 00:19:56,057
Private secretaries shall open
all classifications up to Top Secret.

379
00:19:56,224 --> 00:19:59,182
Only letters marked "personal"
shall remain unopened,

380
00:19:59,344 --> 00:20:01,653
unless the Minister
orders otherwise.

381
00:20:01,864 --> 00:20:03,138
What about Daddy?

382
00:20:05,184 --> 00:20:07,698
Where does yourfather
come into this?

383
00:20:08,304 --> 00:20:10,022
