489
00:25:41,584 --> 00:25:44,382
Pete and I are just going
to ring the press,

490
00:25:44,544 --> 00:25:46,455
then we're off to the Spinney.

491
00:25:46,624 --> 00:25:48,899
Don't do that!
Think of the damage.

492
00:25:49,064 --> 00:25:50,292
What damage?

493
00:25:50,464 --> 00:25:51,977
Well... to me.

494
00:25:52,144 --> 00:25:53,896
To you? Isn't that typical?

495
00:25:54,064 --> 00:25:55,656
What about damage
to badgers?

496
00:25:55,824 --> 00:25:57,860
You're not going
to be exterminated.

497
00:25:58,024 --> 00:26:00,015
Well, in a sense, yes.

498
00:26:00,184 --> 00:26:02,175
Then you knowwhat to do.

499
00:26:02,784 --> 00:26:04,775
- Ten...
- Look... Look...

500
00:26:04,944 --> 00:26:06,093
- Nine...
- Lucy, don't...

501
00:26:06,264 --> 00:26:07,617
- Eight...
- Lucy!

502
00:26:07,784 --> 00:26:10,093
If I could have a word
with the young lady.

503
00:26:10,264 --> 00:26:12,824
Sir Humphrey Appleby
wants a word with you.

504
00:26:12,984 --> 00:26:16,101
- A new development.
- Six... five...

505
00:26:16,904 --> 00:26:19,976
Miss Hacker...
Ah, how do you do?

506
00:26:20,264 --> 00:26:22,016
Humphrey Appleby here.

507
00:26:22,504 --> 00:26:25,655
- Mr. Hacker's Permanent Secretary.
- Five and holding.

508
00:26:25,824 --> 00:26:27,621
If I could just have a word.

509
00:26:27,784 --> 00:26:31,618
I have just seen the latest report
from the Government's inspectors,

510
00:26:31,784 --> 00:26:34,503
which throws new light
on the issue.

511
00:26:34,864 --> 00:26:35,864
Why?

512
00:26:36,024 --> 00:26:39,255
Apparently there is
no badgercolony in Spinney.

513
00:26:39,424 --> 00:26:40,823
Now, it says here

514
00:26:41,504 --> 00:26:45,292
"Last evidence ofbadger
droppings, freshly turned earth

515
00:26:45,464 --> 00:26:47,420
was recorded
eleven years ago".

516
00:26:47,584 --> 00:26:48,653
But the papers...

517
00:26:48,824 --> 00:26:53,022
Apparently the story was fed
to them by a property developer.

518
00:26:53,824 --> 00:26:56,736
- Property developer?
- Yes. The Council has plans

519
00:26:56,904 --> 00:27:00,214
to use the spinneyfora new College
of Further Education,

520
00:27:00,384 --> 00:27:03,820
and the developerwants it
foroffices and luxuryflats.

521
00:27:03,984 --> 00:27:07,260
Well, if it's protected
he won't be able to.

522
00:27:07,424 --> 00:27:09,415
And, norwill the Council.

523
00:27:09,744 --> 00:27:12,816
And he knows they'll use
the moneyforsomething else,

524
00:27:13,064 --> 00:27:16,534
then he can establish
that there's no badgercolony,

525
00:27:16,704 --> 00:27:20,174
get the protection orderremoved
and build his offices.

526
00:27:20,344 --> 00:27:21,697
It's common practice.

527
00:27:22,624 --> 00:27:26,014
So there isn't any wildlife
in the spinney at all?

528
00:27:26,184 --> 00:27:29,540
Well, there is some.
It's been used as a rubbish dump

529
00:27:29,704 --> 00:27:34,255
by people from Wootton Wawen,
so there're lots of rats.

530
00:27:35,104 --> 00:27:38,141
- Rats?
- Yes. Several thousand, actually.

531
00:27:39,184 --> 00:27:42,654
They are wildlife too,
in theirway, aren't they?

532
00:27:42,864 --> 00:27:45,662
Itwould be a pity to play
into the developer's hands.

533
00:27:46,064 --> 00:27:47,861
Yes, I suppose itwould.

534
00:27:48,024 --> 00:27:51,414
Yes, I very much respect
yourviews and yourcommitment.

535
00:27:51,584 --> 00:27:53,461
Would you like to speak
to the Minister?

536
00:27:53,624 --> 00:27:57,299
No, that's all right.
Oh, well. Forget it then.

537
00:28:00,744 --> 00:28:03,258
Humphrey!
I take it all back!

538
00:28:04,344 --> 00:28:07,302
Itwas nothing, Minister.
Itwas all in the files.

539
00:28:07,464 --> 00:28:08,943
A property developer!

540
00:28:09,104 --> 00:28:12,016
The cunning devils...
Let me look at the file!

541
00:28:12,664 --> 00:28:15,861
I don't think
you'd find them interesting.

542
00:28:16,864 --> 00:28:20,095
- Let me have a look.
- No, I don't think you'd...

543
00:28:20,264 --> 00:28:21,538
Humphrey!

544
00:28:22,664 --> 00:28:24,495
Itwas true, wasn't it?

545
00:28:26,024 --> 00:28:29,460
Was there one word of truth
in that whole story

546
00:28:29,624 --> 00:28:31,057
you told to Lucy?

547
00:28:31,304 --> 00:28:34,376
Do you really want me
to answerthat question?

548
00:28:36,424 --> 00:28:37,618
No.

549
00:28:38,904 --> 00:28:40,860
- I don't think I do.
- Quite so.

550
00:28:41,264 --> 00:28:44,813
Perhaps there are some things
it is betterfora Ministernot to know.

